## HackerNews-Specific Guidelines

### Audience
- Target software engineers and technical professionals
- Focus on technical founders and startup technologists
- Consider open source contributors and tech enthusiasts
- Value technical expertise and innovation

### Tone & Voice
- Technical and substantive
- Developer-focused language
- Avoid marketing speak and buzzwords
- Focus on technical merit and innovation
- Encourage critical discussion and debate

### Content Strategy
- Emphasize technical depth and innovation
- Focus on substantive technical content
- Share technical insights and learnings
- Include code examples, technical details, and implementation specifics
- Highlight technical challenges and solutions
- Avoid superficial marketing content

### Engagement Strategy
- Frame content to encourage technical discussion
- Pose technical questions and challenges
- Invite debate and alternative perspectives
- Submit during peak hours (9 AM - 5 PM Pacific)
- Best days: Weekdays (Monday-Friday)
- Use compelling technical headlines

### Formatting
- Use clear, technical language
- Include code blocks when relevant
- Use technical terminology appropriately
- Structure for technical readability
- Include links to technical resources

### What to Avoid
- Marketing language and buzzwords
- Overly promotional content
- Superficial technical content
- Clickbait headlines
- Excessive self-promotion
